        "collapsible_tab_TbRiah": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "heading": "Care & Details",
            "content": "<p>Machine wash cold, do not tumble dry under any circumstances, and avoid ironing or using fabric softeners to maintain the softness and coziness of your blanket for years to come.<br/><br/>Our blankets are made from natural muslin cotton, so slight size variations may occur. Measurements are taken at full stretch.</p><p>To maintain the original size and softness, avoid hot washes — high temperatures can cause shrinkage.</p>",
            "page": "",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "keep_open": false
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab-0": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "heading": "What is Muslin Cotton?",
            "content": "<h4><strong>A Fabric Fit for Royalty</strong></h4><p>Originating from ancient Bengal (modern-day Bangladesh and India), muslin was once so rare and coveted that it was called <em>\"woven wind\"</em>—worn by queens, emperors, and aristocrats who prized its <strong>weightless luxury</strong>. The finest muslin was so sheer it could pass through a ring yet so strong it lasted generations. Today, authentic muslin remains a symbol of <strong>timeless elegance and craftsmanship</strong>.</p><h4><strong>Why Is Muslin Cotton Special?</strong></h4><ul><li><strong>Breathable & Lightweight</strong>: Its loose, open weave allows airflow like no other fabric, making it <strong>perfect for temperature regulation</strong>—cool in summer, cozy in winter.</li><li><strong>Luxuriously Soft</strong>: With every wash, muslin becomes even softer, developing a <strong>vintage, lived-in elegance</strong> that only improves with time.</li><li><strong>Gentle Yet Durable</strong>: Despite its delicate feel, high-quality muslin is surprisingly strong, resisting pulls and tears while maintaining its graceful drape.</li></ul><h4><strong>The Ultimate in Elevated Comfort</strong></h4><p>Our muslin cotton blankets and bedding carry forward this legacy—offering you <strong>a touch of historical opulence with modern comfort</strong>. Whether swaddling a newborn, dressing a luxury bed, or wrapping yourself in a breathable layer, muslin is more than a fabric—it’s an heirloom in the making.</p>",
            "page": "",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "keep_open": false
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab-1": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "icon": "check_mark",
            "heading": "Shipping & Returns",
            "content": "<p>All Orders are fulfilled and then shipped to anywhere in the <strong>US</strong> in <strong>1-3 working days</strong> on average.</p><p>All orders come with tracking information once shipped.</p><p><strong>Returns</strong></p><p>Not happy with your purchase? No worries, we've got you covered!<br/><br/>You may return it within 30 days of delivery for a full refund or exchange, no questions asked. To initiate a return, just contact our customer service team at <a href=\"mailto:support@thefleececompany.com\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"mailto:support@thefleececompany.com\">support@thefleececompany.com</a>.</p>",
            "page": "",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "keep_open": false
          }
        },
